    <text>
        <body>       
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Boston Kislev 26<lb/>
                Hannuca 5649<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I was in New York<lb/> the week before last with my<lb/> children on business &#38; <sic>Ive</sic> fully<lb/> expected to have run over &#38; seen<lb/> you&#44; but was delayed &#38; had to come<lb/> back without that pleasure it<lb/> is quite possibly next week we may<lb/> go over again if so with God<lb/> Blessing we will try &#38; call upon<lb/> you.<lb/></p> 
            <p>We have delayed as I had fully<lb/> expected to have so arranged our<lb/> business to have taken the mortal<lb/> remains of my darling Angel wife<lb/> to the Holy City.  We are having a<lb/> Tombstone <sic>errected</sic> &#38; we would<lb/> be ever grateful if you will kindly<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>draft one for us from the enclosed in<lb/> Hebrew &#38; also write therefrom one<lb/> in English&#44; adding the lines which<lb/> my poor wife had <sic>errected</sic> over her<lb/> own beloved Mother.  If possible you<lb/> could mail it to us on Sunday to<lb/> be here on Monday&#44; we would especially<lb/> esteem it a favor&#44; as the marble<lb/> worker has been so often &#38; I have<lb/> had such a <sic>sensative</sic> feeling I do<lb/> not like the stone to cover up her<lb/> darling remains.  I am feeling at the<lb/> present moment so dull &#38; cannot<lb/> write as my tears are yet as fresh<lb/> as when you meet me in my deep<lb/> sorrow.  God Bless you &#38; all<lb/> dear to you &#38; remain<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours very sincerely<lb/>
                Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
